      <section eId="sec_31_7_177">
        <num>31-7-177</num>
        <content>
          <p>Since hospice care is primarily provided at home, licensure shall not be determined solely on the number of inpatient beds needed for service. Inpatient beds under contract to a hospice program may be used by the hospice when needed but may remain otherwise available to the inpatient unit at other times without a change in licensing.</p>
